translated: Johansson, Sven Robert, bank clerk, principal, Vadstena, b. 1/6/96 in Skövde to commissioner F. J. and his wife G. with maiden name Hinz. Educated in Lund with a specialist course for students at Gothenburg's Handiinst. from 1915-1916. Traveled to Germany in 1928, 1938, and 1939, and to Austria in 1939. Employed by Sydsv. Kredit A-B, working in the Molkom branch from 1918, and in the main office from 1919. Reviewed department accounts in 1922. Hired by Sydsv. Banken, now Skånska Banken, in 1922 and clerk at the Kalmar branch in 1927. Became manager in 1931 for the Ödeshög branch and was in charge of the eastern region for Enskilda Banken in Vadstena since 1938, as well as principal and teacher at Vadstena's vocational school since 1939. Member of the board and treasurer of Vadstena Komm. Cafébol, Johansson, Andersson & Co., and approved as an examiner by the Chamber of Commerce in 1931. Chairman of the finance committee from 1941 to 1944, and member of the city council since 1943, as well as member of the county road commission. Chairman of the Vadstenabygdens cooperative laundry association and member of the Odd Fellow organization.
